Unswervingly uphold and develop socialism with Chinese characteristics
(January 5, 2013)
The issue of the road is the first issue that concerns the success or failure of the party's cause, and the road is the life of the party.
Socialism with Chinese characteristics is the dialectical unity of the theoretical logic of scientific socialism and the historical logic of Chinese social development. The only way to accelerate socialist modernization and realize the great rejuvenation of the Chinese nation.
All Party comrades must adhere to the guidance of Deng Xiaoping Theory, the important thought of "Three Represents", and the Scientific Outlook on Development, unswervingly uphold and develop socialism with Chinese characteristics, adhere to the Marxist view of development, and insist that practice is the only criterion for testing truth, Give full play to the initiative and creativity of history, clearly understand the changes and changes in the world, national conditions, and party conditions, always have the spirit of opening up roads through mountains and building bridges when encountering rivers, forge ahead, explore boldly, and be brave and good at analyzing and answering questions in real life. We will continue to deepen reform and opening up, make discoveries, create and advance, and promote theoretical innovation, practical innovation, and institutional innovation.
The spirit of the 18th National Congress of the Communist Party of China, said a thousand words and ten thousand, boiled down to one point, that is, upholding and developing socialism with Chinese characteristics.
This year marks the 31st anniversary of Comrade Deng Xiaoping's proposal to build socialism with Chinese characteristics.
Comrade Deng Xiaoping pioneered socialism with Chinese characteristics, and for the first time systematically and tentatively answered a series of basic questions about how to build socialism, how to consolidate and develop socialism in a country with relatively backward economy and culture such as China. Inherited and developed Marxism, opened up a new realm of Marxism, and raised the understanding of socialism to a new scientific level.
Socialism with Chinese characteristics is socialism and not any other doctrine. The basic principles of scientific socialism cannot be lost. If you lose it, it will not be socialism.
What kind of doctrine a country implements depends crucially on whether the doctrine can solve the historical issues facing the country.
Both history and reality tell us that only socialism can save China, and only socialism with Chinese characteristics can develop China. This is the conclusion of history and the choice of the people.
With the continuous development of socialism with Chinese characteristics, our system will become more and more mature, the superiority of our socialist system will be further revealed, and our path will become wider and wider.
We just need to have such confidence in the road, in theory, and in the system, so as to truly achieve "strengthening despite thousands of hardships and persevering in the wind from east, west, north and south".
Our Party leads the people in socialist construction. There are two historical periods before and after the reform and opening up. These are two periods that are interrelated and have major differences, but in essence they are both the practice of our Party leading the people in socialist construction. explore.
Socialism with Chinese characteristics was created in the new era of reform and opening up, but it was also created on the basis that the basic socialist system has been established in New China and has been built for more than 20 years.
Although there are great differences in the ideological guidance, principles and policies, and practical work of socialist construction between these two historical periods, the two are by no means separate from each other, nor are they fundamentally opposed.
The historical period after the reform and opening up cannot be used to negate the historical period before the reform and opening up, nor can the historical period before the reform and opening up be used to negate the historical period after the reform and opening up.
It is necessary to adhere to the ideological line of seeking truth from facts, distinguish the mainstream from the tributaries, adhere to the truth, correct mistakes, carry forward experience, and draw lessons, and on this basis, continue to push forward the cause of the party and the people.
Marxism must continue to develop with the development of the times, practice and science, and cannot remain unchanged. Socialism has always been advancing in development.
Upholding and developing socialism with Chinese characteristics is a big article, for which Comrade Deng Xiaoping determined the basic ideas and principles. Great articles have been written on this great article.
Now, the task of our generation of Communists is to continue writing this great article.
Adhering to Marxism and socialism must have a development perspective.
The more our career progresses and develops, the more new situations and problems we will face, the more risks and challenges we will face, and the more unpredictable things we will face.
We must enhance our sense of urgency, and be prepared for danger in times of peace. If we understand, we must understand, and if we do not understand, we must not understand; if we understand, we must strive to create conditions to do it, and if we do not understand, we must hurry up to study and understand.
Communist Party members, especially leading cadres of Party members, should be firm believers and loyal practitioners of the lofty ideal of communism and the common ideal of socialism with Chinese characteristics.
We must not only firmly believe in taking the road of socialism with Chinese characteristics, but also have the lofty ideal of communism in mind, unswervingly implement the basic line and basic program of the party in the primary stage of socialism, and do a good job in every current task.
Revolutionary ideals are higher than the sky.
If you do not have lofty ideals, you are not a qualified Communist Party member; you are not a qualified Communist Party member if you talk about lofty ideals without real work.
