Fifth, reform and opening up is the cause of hundreds of millions of people themselves. We must adhere to respecting the people's pioneering spirit and insist on advancing under the leadership of the Party.
Every breakthrough and development in the understanding and practice of reform and opening up, the emergence and development of every new thing in reform and opening up, the creation and accumulation of experience in every aspect of reform and opening up, all come from the practice and wisdom of hundreds of millions of people.
The more arduous the task of reform, development and stability is, the more we must strengthen and improve the party's leadership, the more we must maintain the flesh-and-blood ties between the party and the people, be good at leading the people forward by proposing and implementing correct lines, principles and policies, and be good at creating and developing from the people's practice It is necessary to improve policies and propositions in the requirements, so that the achievements of reform and development will benefit all the people more and more equitably, and continuously consolidate the mass foundation for deepening reform and opening up.
The reform and opening up can only be carried out when it is not completed.
Without reform and opening up, China would not be where it is today, and there would be no China tomorrow.
The contradictions in the reform and opening up can only be solved by the method of reform and opening up.
We must fully implement the spirit of the 18th National Congress of the Communist Party of China, adhere to the guidance of Deng Xiaoping Theory, the important thought of "Three Represents", and the Scientific Outlook on Development, actively respond to the strong voices and ardent expectations of the broad masses of the people for deepening reform and opening up, and build social consensus. Coordinate and promote reforms in all fields and links, and strive to push reform and opening up forward.
Explanation on the "Decision of the Central Committee of the Communist Party of China on Several Major Issues Concerning Comprehensively Deepening the Reform"
(November 9, 2013)
Entrusted by the Political Bureau of the CPC Central Committee, I will now explain to the plenary session the "Decision of the CPC Central Committee on Several Major Issues Concerning Comprehensively Deepening the Reform".
I. About the drafting process of the plenary decision
Since the reform and opening up, what topics were studied, what decisions were made, what measures were taken, and what signals were released at the Third Plenary Sessions of the Central Committee of the CPC Central Committee. Years of work are of great significance.
After the 18th National Congress of the Communist Party of China, the Central Committee began to consider the topics of the Third Plenary Session of the 18th Central Committee.
The 18th National Congress of the Communist Party of China put forward the goal of building a moderately prosperous society in an all-round way and deepening reform and opening up in an all-round way, emphasizing that we must use greater political courage and wisdom to seize the opportunity to deepen reforms in important areas, and resolutely eliminate all ideological and institutional drawbacks that hinder scientific development. , to build a system that is complete, scientific and standardized, and operates effectively, so that all aspects of the system are more mature and finalized.
We believe that in order to complete the strategic goals and work arrangements proposed at the 18th National Congress of the Communist Party of China, we must press ahead with comprehensive reforms.
It has been 35 years since the Third Plenary Session of the Eleventh Central Committee of the Communist Party of China made the historic decision to shift the work center of the Party and the state to economic construction and implement reform and opening up.
The face of the Chinese people, the face of socialist China, and the face of the Communist Party of China can undergo such profound changes, and my country can win a pivotal position in the international community, relying on the unremitting promotion of reform and opening up.
In 1992, Comrade Deng Xiaoping said in the southern talk: "If you don't adhere to socialism, if you don't reform and open up, if you don't develop the economy, if you don't improve the people's life, you will only be a dead end."
Looking back, we have a deeper understanding of what Comrade Deng Xiaoping said.
Therefore, we say that only socialism can save China, and only reform and opening up can develop China, develop socialism, and develop Marxism.
It is precisely from the perspective of historical experience and practical needs that since the 18th National Congress of the Communist Party of China, the Central Committee has repeatedly emphasized that reform and opening up is the key move to determine the fate of contemporary China, and it is also a decision to achieve the "two centenary goals" and the realization of the Chinese nation. The key to the great rejuvenation is that the development of practice will never end, the emancipation of the mind will never end, and the reform and opening up will never end. There is no way out for stagnation and retrogression.
In the face of the new situation and new tasks, we must comprehensively deepen reforms, focus on solving a series of prominent contradictions and problems faced by our country's development, and continuously promote the self-improvement and development of the socialist system with Chinese characteristics.
At present, the domestic and international environment is undergoing extremely extensive and profound changes. my country's development faces a series of prominent contradictions and challenges, and there are still many difficulties and problems on the way forward.
For example, unbalanced, uncoordinated, and unsustainable problems in development are still prominent, technological innovation capabilities are not strong, industrial structure is unreasonable, development methods are still extensive, the development gap between urban and rural areas and the income distribution gap between residents is still large, and social conflicts have increased significantly. Education, employment, social security, medical care, housing, ecological environment, food and drug safety, safety in production, social security, law enforcement and justice, etc. have many issues that concern the vital interests of the masses. The problem of extravagance is prominent, negative corruption is prone to occur frequently in some areas, the fight against corruption is still grim, and so on.
To solve these problems, the key lies in deepening reforms.
In April of this year, the Political Bureau of the Central Committee decided to study and make a decision on comprehensively deepening the reform at the Third Plenary Session of the 18th CPC Central Committee after in-depth thinking and research, as well as extensive listening to the opinions of all parties inside and outside the party.
On April 20, the Central Committee issued the "Notice on soliciting opinions on the issue of comprehensively deepening the reform at the Third Plenary Session of the 18th CPC Central Committee".
All regions and departments agreed that the Third Plenary Session of the 18th CPC Central Committee focused on the issue of comprehensively deepening the reform, which complied with the wishes of the majority of Party members, cadres, and the masses, and grasped the issues of greatest concern to the whole society.
Since the reform and opening up, the Third Plenary Sessions of the Central Committee of the Communist Party of China have studied and discussed the issue of deepening reform, all of which are sending an important signal that our party will unswervingly hold high the banner of reform and opening up, and unswervingly adhere to the theory since the Third Plenary Session of the Eleventh Central Committee of the Party. and route policy.
In the final analysis, it is to answer the question of what flag to raise and what road to take under the new historical conditions.
The Third Plenary Session of the Eighteenth Central Committee of the Communist Party of China took comprehensively deepening reform as the main topic. It is our party's adherence to Deng Xiaoping Theory, the important thought of "Three Represents", and the Scientific Outlook on Development as the guide to unswervingly implement the party's basic line in the new situation. , basic program, basic experience, basic requirements, an important declaration and important manifestation of unswervingly holding high the banner of reform and opening up.
After the topic was determined, the Political Bureau of the Central Committee decided to set up a document drafting team, with me as the team leader, Liu Yunshan and Zhang Gaoli as the deputy team leaders, responsible comrades from relevant departments, and some provincial and municipal leaders to participate, under the leadership of the Standing Committee of the Political Bureau of the Central Committee. The plenary decides on the drafting work.
Since the establishment of the document drafting group, for nearly 7 months, it has widely solicited opinions, carried out special demonstrations, conducted investigations and researches, and repeatedly discussed and revised.
During this period, three meetings of the Standing Committee of the Political Bureau of the CPC Central Committee and two meetings of the Political Bureau of the Central Committee respectively deliberated and decided, and the draft was also distributed to a certain range of the party for comments, soliciting the opinions of old comrades in the party, and specifically listening to the Central Committee of the democratic parties and the whole country. The heads of the Federation of Industry and Commerce and the opinions of non-partisan persons.
Judging from the feedback, all parties agreed that the decision of the plenary session deeply analyzed the major theoretical and practical problems facing my country's reform, development and stability, clarified the significance and future direction of comprehensively deepening the reform, and put forward the guiding ideology, goals and tasks for comprehensively deepening the reform. , major principles, depicting a new blueprint, new vision, and new goals for comprehensively deepening reforms, bringing together new ideas, new judgments, and new measures for comprehensively deepening reforms, reflecting social voices, social demands, and social expectations. The ideological consensus and action wisdom of the whole society on comprehensively deepening the reform.
All parties agreed that the decision of the plenary session rationally laid out the strategic priorities, priorities, main directions, working mechanisms, promotion methods, timetables, and roadmaps for comprehensively deepening the reform, and formed a series of new major breakthroughs in reform theories and policies. Another general deployment and general mobilization of comprehensively deepening the reform will definitely have a significant and far-reaching impact on promoting the development of socialism with Chinese characteristics.
During the process of soliciting opinions, many good opinions and suggestions were put forward.
The Central Committee instructed the document drafting group to carefully sort out and study these opinions and suggestions, and the document drafting group made important revisions to the decision of the plenary session.
2. The overall framework and key issues for the decision of the plenary session
The Political Bureau of the Central Committee believes that in the face of the new situation, new tasks and new requirements, the key to comprehensively deepening reforms is to further form a development environment for fair competition, further enhance the vitality of economic and social development, further improve government efficiency and effectiveness, and further realize social fairness and justice. Promote social harmony and stability, and further improve the party's leadership and governance capacity.
Focusing on these major topics, we emphasize that we must have a strong awareness of problems, take major problems as the guide, grasp key issues for further research and thinking, and strive to solve a series of prominent contradictions and problems facing my country's development.
We Chinese Communists have always done revolution, construction, and reform to solve China's real problems.
It can be said that the reform was forced by the problem and deepened in the continuous solution of the problem.
Over the past 35 years, we have solved a series of problems in the development of the party and the country through reform.
At the same time, in the process of understanding and transforming the world, old problems are solved, new problems will arise, and the system always needs to be continuously improved. Therefore, reform cannot be accomplished overnight or once and for all.
The plenary meeting decided to draft, highlighting five aspects of consideration.
The first is to adapt to the new requirements of the development of the party and the country, and implement the strategic task of comprehensively deepening reform and opening up put forward by the 18th National Congress of the Communist Party of China.
The second is to take the reform as the main line and highlight the new measures for comprehensively deepening the reform. General measures, repetitive measures, and purely developmental measures are not included.
The third is to grasp the key points, focus on solving the problems strongly reflected by the people, respond to the voices and expectations of the people, highlight important areas and key links, and highlight the leading role of economic system reform.
The fourth is to insist on being active and prudent, and to design reform measures with boldness and steady steps.
The fifth is to design the time to 2020, propose reform tasks according to this time period, and achieve decisive results in the reform of important areas and key links by 2020.
In terms of frame structure, the plenary meeting decided to take the major issues that need to be solved urgently as the main points, and plan the layout according to the rules.
In addition to the introduction and conclusion, there are 16 parts in total, divided into three major sections.
The first part constitutes the first section, which is the general theory, which mainly expounds the significance, guiding ideology and general thinking of comprehensively deepening the reform.
Parts 2 to 15 constitute the second section, which is a sub-thesis, mainly from the six aspects of economy, politics, culture, society, ecological civilization, national defense and the army, and specifically deploys the main tasks and major measures for comprehensively deepening the reform.
Among them, there are 6 articles in the economic aspect (Parts 2 to 7), 3 articles in the political aspect (Parts 8 through 10), 1 article in the cultural aspect (Part 11), and 2 articles in the social aspect (Part 10). Sections 12 to 13), 1 article on ecology (section 14), and 1 article on national defense and the military (section 15).
The sixteenth part constitutes the third section, which is about organization and leadership, mainly expounding on strengthening and improving the Party's leadership in comprehensively deepening the reform.
Here, I would like to introduce the central government's consideration on several major issues and major measures involved in the decision of the plenary session.
First, it is about making the market play a decisive role in resource allocation and better playing the role of the government.
This is a major theoretical point raised by the decision of this plenary meeting.
This is because the reform of the economic system is still the focus of comprehensively deepening the reform, and the core issue of the reform of the economic system is still to properly handle the relationship between the government and the market.
In 1992, the 14th National Congress of the Communist Party of China proposed that the goal of my country's economic system reform is to establish a socialist market economic system, and proposed that the market should play a fundamental role in resource allocation under the state's macro-control.
This major theoretical breakthrough has played an extremely important role in my country's reform and opening up and economic and social development.
This also shows that theoretical innovation plays an important leading role in practical innovation, and the comprehensive deepening of reform must be guided by theoretical innovation.
After more than 20 years of practice, my country's socialist market economic system has been initially established, but there are still many problems, mainly because the market order is not standardized, and the phenomenon of seeking economic benefits by illegal means is widespread; the development of the production factor market is lagging behind, and the factors are idle and A large number of effective demands are not met and coexist; market rules are not uniform, sectoral protectionism and local protectionism exist in large numbers; market competition is insufficient, which hinders the survival of the fittest and structural adjustment, and so on.
If these problems are not solved well, it will be difficult to form a perfect socialist market economic system.
In the more than 20 years since the 14th National Congress of the Communist Party of China, we have been looking for a new scientific orientation based on practical expansion and deepening understanding of the relationship between the government and the market.
The 15th National Congress of the Communist Party of China proposed to "make the market play a fundamental role in resource allocation under the state's macro-control", and the 16th National Congress of the Party proposed to "give full play to the fundamental role of the market in resource allocation to a greater extent". The Seventh National Congress of the Communist Party of China proposed to "better play the fundamental role of the market in resource allocation from an institutional perspective", and the Eighteenth National Congress of the Communist Party of China proposed to "give full play to the fundamental role of the market in resource allocation to a greater extent and a wider range".
It can be seen that our understanding of the relationship between the government and the market is also deepening.
In the course of this discussion and soliciting opinions, many parties suggested that the relationship between the government and the market should be further positioned in theory, which will play a very important role in comprehensively deepening the reform.
Considering various opinions and practical development requirements, after repeated discussions and studies, the central government believes that the conditions for making a new theoretical statement on this issue are ripe, and the "basic role" of the market in resource allocation should be changed to "decisive role" .
At present, my country's socialist market economic system has been initially established, the degree of marketization has been greatly improved, our understanding and control of market laws have been continuously improved, the macro-control system has become more complete, and the subjective and objective conditions are in place. We should improve the socialist market. New steps have been taken in the economic system.
To further handle the relationship between the government and the market, in fact, it is necessary to handle the issue of whether the market plays a decisive role or the government plays a decisive role in resource allocation.
Economic development is to improve the allocation efficiency of resources, especially scarce resources, to produce as many products as possible with as few resources as possible, and to obtain the greatest possible benefits.
Both theory and practice have proved that market allocation of resources is the most efficient form.
The market determines the allocation of resources is a general law of the market economy, and the market economy is essentially an economy in which the market determines the allocation of resources.
To improve the socialist market economic system, we must follow this rule and focus on solving the problems of imperfect market system, excessive government intervention and inadequate supervision.
The positioning of "making the market play a decisive role in the allocation of resources" is conducive to establishing a correct concept of the relationship between the government and the market in the whole party and the whole society, and is conducive to the transformation of the economic development mode, the transformation of government functions, and the suppression of passive corruption. Phenomenon.
Of course, our country implements a socialist market economy system, and we must still insist on giving full play to the superiority of our socialist system and the positive role of the party and government.
The market plays a decisive role in resource allocation, but not all.
To develop a socialist market economy, both the role of the market and the role of the government should be brought into play, but the functions of the market and the government are different.
The decision of the plenary session put forward clear requirements for better exerting the role of the government, emphasizing that scientific macro-control and effective government governance are inherent requirements for giving full play to the advantages of the socialist market economy system.
The Plenary Session decided to make arrangements to improve the macro-control system, fully and correctly perform government functions, and optimize the organizational structure of the government, emphasizing that the government's responsibilities and roles are mainly to maintain macroeconomic stability, strengthen and optimize public services, ensure fair competition, strengthen market supervision, and maintain market order, promote sustainable development, promote common prosperity, and make up for market failures.
The second is about upholding and improving the basic economic system.
Adhering to and improving the basic economic system in which public ownership is the mainstay and multiple forms of ownership develop together is an important pillar for consolidating and developing the socialist system with Chinese characteristics.
Since the reform and opening up, my country's ownership structure has been gradually adjusted, and the proportions of the public and non-public economies in economic development and employment promotion have been constantly changing, enhancing the vitality of economic and social development.
Under such circumstances, how to better reflect and adhere to the dominant position of public ownership, and how to further explore the effective realization of the basic economic system, is a major issue before us.
The decision of the plenary meeting emphasized the need to unswervingly consolidate and develop the public sector of the economy, adhere to the dominant position of the public sector, give play to the leading role of the state-owned economy, and continuously enhance the vitality, control and influence of the state-owned economy.
The plenary session decided to adhere to and develop the relevant discussions since the 15th National Congress of the Communist Party of China, proposed to actively develop the mixed-ownership economy, and emphasized that the mixed-ownership economy with cross-shareholding and mutual integration of state-owned capital, collective capital, and non-public capital is an important part of the basic economic system. The form of realization is conducive to the amplification of functions of state-owned capital, the preservation and appreciation of value, and the improvement of competitiveness.
This is an effective way and an inevitable choice to uphold the dominant status of public ownership and enhance the vitality, control and influence of the state-owned economy under the new situation.
The plenary meeting decided to improve the state-owned assets management system, focus on capital management, strengthen state-owned asset supervision, and reform the authorized operation system of state-owned capital; the investment and operation of state-owned capital should serve the national strategic goals, and invest more in important matters related to national security and the lifeline of the national economy. Industries and key areas, focusing on providing public services, developing important and forward-looking strategic industries, protecting the ecological environment, supporting scientific and technological progress, and safeguarding national security; transferring part of state-owned capital to enrich social security funds; increasing the proportion of state-owned capital income turned over to public finance, and more. It is mostly used to protect and improve people's livelihood.
State-owned enterprises are an important force in promoting the modernization of the country and safeguarding the common interests of the people.
After years of reform, state-owned enterprises have generally been integrated with the market economy.
At the same time, state-owned enterprises have accumulated some problems and drawbacks, and further reforms are needed.
The plenary session decided to propose a series of targeted reform measures, including increasing the investment of state-owned capital in public welfare enterprises; the natural monopoly industries where state-owned capital continues to control and operate, implement the separation of government and enterprise, separation of government and capital, franchising, and government supervision. The main content of the reform is to separate network operations and open up competitive businesses according to the characteristics of different industries; improve the corporate governance structure of coordinated operation and effective checks and balances; establish a professional manager system to better play the role of entrepreneurs; establish long-term incentives and constraints Mechanism, strengthen the accountability of state-owned enterprises for operation and investment; explore and promote the disclosure of major information such as financial budgets of state-owned enterprises; state-owned enterprises should reasonably increase the proportion of market-based selection and employment, and reasonably determine and strictly regulate the salary level, job treatment, job consumption, business consumption.
These measures will promote state-owned enterprises to improve the modern enterprise system, improve operational efficiency, reasonably assume social responsibilities, and play a better role.
Adhering to and improving the basic economic system must adhere to the "two unshakable".
The plenary meeting decided to put forward reform measures to encourage, support and guide the development of the non-public economy and stimulate the vitality and creativity of the non-public economy from multiple levels.
In terms of functional positioning, it is clear that both the public economy and the non-public economy are an important part of the socialist market economy and an important basis for my country's economic and social development; in terms of property rights protection, it is clearly stated that the property rights of the public economy are inviolable, and the non-public economy property rights are inviolable. It is also inviolable; in terms of policy treatment, it emphasizes adherence to equal rights, equal opportunities, and equal rules, and implements a unified market access system; encourages non-public enterprises to participate in the reform of state-owned enterprises, encourages the development of mixed-ownership enterprises controlled by non-public capital, and encourages non-public enterprises to participate in the reform of state-owned enterprises. conditions for private enterprises to establish a modern enterprise system.
This will promote the healthy development of the non-public economy.
Third, on deepening the reform of the fiscal and taxation system.
Finance is the foundation and important pillar of national governance, and a scientific fiscal and taxation system is the institutional guarantee for optimizing resource allocation, maintaining market unity, promoting social fairness, and achieving long-term national stability.
The current fiscal and taxation system was gradually perfected and formed on the basis of the tax-sharing system reform in 1994, and has played an important role in realizing the win-win goal of increasing government financial resources and rapid economic development.
As the situation develops and changes, the current fiscal and taxation system has not fully adapted to the objective requirements of rationally dividing central and local powers and improving national governance, nor fully adapted to the practical needs of changing the mode of economic development and promoting sustainable and healthy economic and social development. Some of the outstanding contradictions and problems in the government are also related to the imperfect fiscal and taxation system.
The reform of the fiscal and taxation system is one of the priorities in this comprehensive deepening of reform.
It mainly involves improving the budget management system, improving the taxation system, and establishing a system that matches the powers and expenditure responsibilities.
The plenary meeting decided to implement a comprehensive, standardized, open and transparent budget system, appropriately strengthen the central authority and expenditure responsibilities, and take national defense, foreign affairs, national security, and national unified market rules and management as the central authority; some social security, cross-regional major projects Construction and maintenance are the common powers of the central and local governments, and gradually straighten out the relationship between powers and powers; the central government can entrust some of the powers and expenditures to local governments by arranging transfer payments; for public services that cross regions and have a greater impact on other regions, the central government undertakes the responsibility through transfer payments Part of the local authority expenditure responsibility.
The main purpose of these reform measures is to clarify powers, reform the tax system, stabilize tax burden, transparent budget, improve efficiency, and speed up the formation of a modern fiscal system that is conducive to the transformation of economic development mode, the establishment of a fair and unified market, and the promotion of equalization of basic public services. To form a fiscal and taxation system that matches the financial resources and powers of the central and local governments, and give better play to the enthusiasm of the central and local governments.
The reform of the fiscal and taxation system requires a process that will be gradually implemented.
The central government has made it clear that it is necessary to maintain the overall stability of the existing central and local financial resources, and to further rationalize the division of central and local revenue.
Fourth, on improving the integrated system and mechanism of urban and rural development.
Unbalanced and uncoordinated urban and rural development is a prominent contradiction in my country's economic and social development, and a major problem that must be solved in building a moderately prosperous society in an all-round way and accelerating socialist modernization.
Since the reform and opening up, my country's rural landscape has undergone earth-shaking changes.
However, the urban-rural dual structure has not fundamentally changed, and the trend of the growing gap between urban and rural development has not fundamentally reversed.
To fundamentally solve these problems, we must promote the integration of urban and rural development.
The Plenary Session decided that it is necessary to improve the system and mechanism, to form a new type of industrial-agricultural-urban-rural relationship that promotes agriculture through industry, urban and rural areas, mutual benefits between industry and agriculture, and integration of urban and rural areas, so that farmers can equally participate in the modernization process and share the fruits of modernization.
The plenary meeting decided to put forward reform measures to improve the integrated system and mechanism of urban and rural development.
The first is to accelerate the construction of a new agricultural management system.
The main purpose is to adhere to the basic position of family management in agriculture, encourage the transfer of land contract management rights to large professional households, family farms, farmers' cooperatives, and agricultural enterprises in the open market, encourage the development of cooperative economy in rural areas, and encourage and guide industrial and commercial capital to develop in rural areas. The modern planting and breeding industry, which is suitable for enterprise-oriented management, allows farmers to use the land contract management rights to invest in the development of agricultural industrialized management.
The second is to give farmers more property rights.
The main purpose is to safeguard farmers' right to contract and manage land in accordance with the law, protect the rights of members of farmers' collective economic organizations, protect farmers' usufructuary rights on their homesteads, and prudently and prudently promote the pilot program of mortgage, guarantee, and transfer of farmers' housing property rights.
The third is to promote the equal exchange of urban and rural factors and the balanced allocation of public resources.
Mainly to ensure equal pay for equal work for migrant workers and ensure that farmers share the land value-added income fairly; improve the agricultural insurance system; encourage social capital to invest in rural construction, and allow enterprises and social organizations to set up various undertakings in rural areas; coordinate the balanced allocation of urban and rural compulsory education resources, and integrate urban and rural residents. The basic old-age insurance system and the basic medical insurance system, promote the coordinated development of the urban and rural minimum living security system, steadily promote the full coverage of the permanent population of urban basic public services, and fully integrate the farmers who have settled in cities into the urban housing and social security system.
Fifth, on promoting the extensive and multi-level institutionalized development of consultative democracy.
Consultative democracy is a unique form and unique advantage of my country's socialist democratic politics, and an important manifestation of the party's mass line in the political field.
Promoting consultative democracy is conducive to improving the orderly political participation of the people, strengthening the flesh-and-blood ties between the party and the people, and promoting scientific and democratic decision-making.
The plenary session decided to promote the extensive and multi-level institutionalized development of consultative democracy as an important part of the reform of the political system. , and insist on consultation before and during decision-making.
It is necessary to build a consultative democracy system with reasonable procedures and complete links, expand the consultation channels of state power organs, CPPCC organizations, party groups, grass-roots organizations, and social organizations; carry out in-depth legislative consultation, administrative consultation, democratic consultation, political participation consultation, and social consultation; The important role of the united front in deliberative democracy, give full play to the role of the CPPCC as an important channel for deliberative democracy, improve the system of the CPPCC, standardize the content and procedures of consultation, expand the form of deliberative democracy, and organize special consultations, counterpart consultations, and consultations in a more active and orderly manner. Sector consultation and proposal handling consultation to increase the density of consultations and improve the effectiveness of consultations.
Sixth, on reforming the judicial system and operating mechanism.
The judicial system is an important part of the political system.
Over the years, the opinions of the masses on judicial injustice have been concentrated, and the lack of judicial credibility is largely related to the unreasonable judicial system and working mechanism.
Judicial reform is one of the focuses of this comprehensive deepening reform.
The decision of the plenary meeting put forward a series of interrelated new measures, including reforming the judicial management system, promoting the unified management of people, property and property in local courts and procuratorates below the provincial level, exploring the establishment of a judicial jurisdiction system that is properly separated from administrative divisions; improving the operation mechanism of judicial power and improving the main The trial judge and collegial panel have a case-handling responsibility system, allowing the judges to make judgments and the judges are responsible; strictly regulate the procedures for commutation, parole, and medical parole; improve the mechanism for preventing, correcting, and investigating wrongful cases, and strictly implement the rule of exclusion of illegal evidence; establish law-related lawsuits and petitions End the system in accordance with the law; abolish the re-education through labor system, improve the punishment and correction laws for illegal and criminal acts, and so on.
These reform measures are of great significance to ensure that judicial organs independently exercise judicial and procuratorial powers in accordance with the law, improve the judicial power operation mechanism with clear rights and responsibilities, improve judicial transparency and credibility, and better protect human rights.
Seventh, on improving the anti-corruption leadership system and working mechanism.
The issue of anti-corruption has always been the subject of much discussion inside and outside the party.
The main problems at present are that the functions of anti-corruption agencies are scattered and do not form a synergy, some cases are difficult to be resolutely investigated and dealt with, and there are frequent corruption cases but insufficient accountability.
The plenary meeting decided to focus on strengthening the innovation of anti-corruption systems and mechanisms and institutional guarantees.
The main purpose is to strengthen the unified leadership of the Party over the construction of a clean government and the anti-corruption work, clarify that the Party Committee is responsible for the main body and the Disciplinary Committee is responsible for supervision, and formulate and implement a practical accountability system; improve the anti-corruption leadership system and working mechanism, and reform and improve all levels The function of the anti-corruption coordination group stipulates that the investigation and handling of corruption cases should be dominated by the leadership of the higher-level disciplinary committee; it reflects the strengthening of the leadership of the higher-level disciplinary committee over the lower-level disciplinary committee, and stipulates that clue handling and case investigation must be reported to the party committee at the same level. The Commission for Discipline Inspection dispatched disciplinary inspection agencies to the party and state organs at the central level to improve the inspection system of the central government and provinces, regions and municipalities, so as to cover all localities, departments, enterprises and institutions.
These measures are put forward on the basis of summarizing practical experience and absorbing opinions from various quarters.
Eighth, on accelerating the improvement of the Internet management leadership system.
Network and information security involves national security and social stability, and is a new comprehensive challenge we face.
From a practical point of view, in the face of the rapid development of Internet technology and applications, the current management system has obvious drawbacks, mainly multiple management, overlapping functions, different powers and responsibilities, and low efficiency.
At the same time, with the increasingly strong attributes of Internet media, online media management and industry management are far from keeping up with the development and changes of the situation.
Especially in the face of the rapid growth of users of social networks and instant messaging tools such as microblogs and WeChat, which have fast dissemination, great influence, wide coverage, and strong social mobilization ability, how to strengthen the construction of online legal system and public opinion guidance to ensure the order of online information dissemination and the national Security and social stability have become prominent real problems before us.
The plenary meeting decided to put forward the policy of adhering to active utilization, scientific development, management according to law, and ensuring safety, intensifying efforts to manage the network according to law, and improving the leadership system of Internet management.
The purpose is to integrate the functions of relevant institutions, form a joint force of Internet management from technology to content, from daily security to crime fighting, and ensure the correct use and security of the network.
Ninth, on the establishment of the National Security Council.
National security and social stability are the prerequisites for reform and development.
Only with national security and social stability can reform and development continue to advance.
At present, my country is facing the dual pressure of safeguarding national sovereignty, security and development interests externally and maintaining political security and social stability internally, and various predictable and unforeseeable risk factors have increased significantly.
However, our security work system and mechanism cannot meet the needs of maintaining national security, and we need to build a strong platform to coordinate national security work.
The establishment of the National Security Committee to strengthen the centralized and unified leadership of the national security work has become a top priority.
The main responsibilities of the National Security Committee are to formulate and implement national security strategies, promote the construction of the national security rule of law, formulate national security work guidelines and policies, and study and solve major problems in national security work.
Tenth, on improving the national natural resource asset management system and improving the natural resource supervision system.
Improving the national natural resource asset management system is a major reform to improve the property rights system for natural resource assets, and it is also an inherent requirement for establishing a systematic and complete ecological civilization system.
Some prominent problems in my country's ecological and environmental protection are related to the imperfect system to a certain extent. One of the reasons is that the owners of natural resource assets owned by the whole people are not in place, and the rights and interests of the owners are not implemented.
In response to this problem, the Plenary Session decided to put forward requirements for improving the national natural resource asset management system.
The general idea is to implement the ownership of natural resource assets owned by the whole people and establish a system for uniformly exercising the responsibilities of the owners of natural resource assets owned by the whole people in accordance with the principle of separation of owners and managers and management of one matter by one department.
The state exercising ownership and management of natural resource assets owned by the whole people is different from the state exercising the right to supervise natural resources within the territory of the country. The former is the right in the sense of the owner, and the latter is the power in the sense of the manager.
This requires perfecting the natural resource supervision system, uniformly exercising the control responsibilities of all land and space uses, and making state-owned natural resource asset owners and state natural resource managers independent, cooperating and supervising each other.
We must realize that mountains, rivers, forests, fields and lakes are a community of life. The lifeblood of people is in the fields, the lifeblood of the fields is in the water, the lifeblood of the water is in the mountains, the lifeblood of the mountains is in the soil, and the lifeblood of the soil is in the trees.
Use control and ecological restoration must follow the laws of nature. If those who plant trees only focus on planting trees, those who control water only manage water, and those who protect fields simply protect fields, it is easy to take care of one thing and lose the other, and eventually cause systematic ecological damage.
A single department is responsible for the control of all land and space uses within the territory, and it is very necessary to uniformly protect and restore mountains, rivers, forests, fields and lakes.
Eleventh, on the establishment of a comprehensive deepening reform leading group by the central government.
Comprehensively deepening the reform is a complex systematic project, and it is often impossible to rely on one or several departments alone, which requires the establishment of a higher-level leadership mechanism.
The plenary meeting decided that the central government should set up a leading group for comprehensively deepening the reform, which will be responsible for the overall design, overall coordination, overall promotion, and supervision of the implementation of the reform.
This is to give better play to the party's core leadership role in overseeing the overall situation and coordinating all parties, and to ensure the smooth progress of reform and the implementation of various reform tasks.
The main responsibilities of the leading group are: unified deployment of major nationwide reforms, overall promotion of reforms in various fields, coordination of various forces to form a joint force for promoting reforms, strengthening supervision and inspection, and promoting the full implementation of reform goals and tasks.
