Conscientiously unify the thinking into the spirit of the Third Plenary Session of the Eighteenth Central Committee of the Communist Party of China
(November 12, 2013)
Only when the thoughts and wills of the whole party are unified can the thoughts and wills of the people of all ethnic groups in the country be unified, and a powerful force for advancing reform can be formed.
Here, around the guiding ideology, general thinking, and goals and tasks put forward by the plenary session, I put forward a few requirements for implementing the spirit of the plenary session.
First, insist on improving and developing the socialist system with Chinese characteristics and advancing the modernization of the national governance system and governance capacity as the general goal of comprehensively deepening reforms.
Comrade Deng Xiaoping proposed in 1992 that it would take another 30 years for us to form a more mature and stereotyped system in all aspects.
On the basis of Comrade Deng Xiaoping's strategic thinking, this plenary session proposed to promote the modernization of the country's governance system and governance capacity.
This is an inevitable requirement for the improvement and development of the socialist system with Chinese characteristics, and the proper meaning of realizing socialist modernization.
The reason why we decided to study the issue of comprehensively deepening the reform at the Third Plenary Session of the Central Committee is not to promote reform in one area, nor to promote reform in several areas, but to promote reform in all areas, that is, from the overall perspective of the country's governance system and governance capacity.
The national governance system and governance capacity are the concentrated expression of a country's system and system execution capacity.
The national governance system is an institutional system that manages the country under the leadership of the party, including the economic, political, cultural, social, ecological civilization and party building and other fields of institutional mechanisms, legal and regulatory arrangements, that is, a set of closely linked and coordinated countries. Institutions; national governance capacity is the ability to use national institutions to manage all aspects of society, including reform, development and stability, internal affairs, foreign affairs and national defense, governance of the party, the country and the army.
The national governance system and governance capacity are an organic whole and complement each other. Only with a good national governance system can the governance capacity be improved, and only by improving the national governance capacity can the effectiveness of the national governance system be brought into full play.
In fact, how to govern a brand-new society such as a socialist society has not been solved very well in the previous world socialism.
Marx and Engels did not encounter the practice of comprehensively governing a socialist country, and many of their principles about the future society were predictive; Lenin died shortly after the October Revolution in Russia, and did not have time to explore this issue in depth; It has been explored and some practical experience has been obtained, but serious mistakes have also been made, and the problem has not been solved.
After our party came to power in the whole country, it has continuously explored this issue. Although there have been serious twists and turns, it has accumulated rich experience and achieved major results in the national governance system and governance capacity. The progress since the reform and opening up has been particularly remarkable.
my country's political stability, economic development, social harmony, and ethnic unity are in stark contrast to the continuing chaos in some regions and countries in the world.
This shows that our national governance system and governance capacity are generally good, and are adapted to my country's national conditions and development requirements.
At the same time, we must also see that compared with the requirements of my country's economic and social development, compared with the expectations of the people, compared with the increasingly fierce international competition in today's world, compared with the realization of long-term national stability, we still have many things in terms of national governance system and governance capacity. Inadequate, there are many areas that need to be improved.
To truly achieve social harmony and stability and the country's long-term stability, it still depends on the system, on our superb ability in national governance, and on a team of high-quality cadres.
To better leverage the advantages of the socialist system with Chinese characteristics, we must modernize the country's governance system and governance capabilities in all fields.
Promoting the modernization of the national governance system and governance capacity is to adapt to the changes of the times, not only reforming the systems and mechanisms, laws and regulations that do not meet the requirements of practical development, but also constantly building new systems, mechanisms, laws and regulations to make all aspects of the system more scientific and more complete, Realize the institutionalization, standardization and procedure of governance of various affairs of the party, state and society.
It is necessary to pay more attention to the building of governance capacity, enhance the awareness of handling affairs according to the system and the law, be good at using the system and the law to govern the country, transform the advantages of various systems into the efficiency of managing the country, and improve the party's scientific, democratic, and law-based governance.
Second, further emancipate the mind, further emancipate and develop social productive forces, and further emancipate and enhance social vitality.
The "three further liberations" proposed by the decision of the plenary session are both the purpose of reform and the conditions for reform.
Emancipating the mind is the premise and the general switch to liberate and develop social productive forces and liberate and enhance social vitality.
Without the emancipation of the mind, our party would not have been able to make the historic decision to shift the center of the work of the party and the state to economic construction and implement reform and opening up shortly after the ten-year turmoil, thus ushering in a new historical period of our country's development; without emancipation of the mind, our party It is impossible to continuously promote theoretical innovation and practical innovation in practice, effectively resolve various risks and challenges on the way forward, continuously push forward reform and opening up, and always be at the forefront of the times.
Emancipating and developing social productive forces and emancipating and enhancing social vitality are the inevitable result of emancipating the mind and an important basis for emancipating the mind.
To build a moderately prosperous society in an all-round way, realize socialist modernization, and realize the great rejuvenation of the Chinese nation, the most fundamental and urgent task is to further liberate and develop social productive forces.
Emancipating the mind, liberating and enhancing social vitality is to better liberate and develop social productive forces.
Comrade Deng Xiaoping said: Revolution is the liberation of productive forces, and reform is also the liberation of productive forces. "After the establishment of the basic socialist system, we must fundamentally change the economic system that restricts the development of productive forces, establish a socialist economic system full of vigor and vitality, and promote the development of productive forces. develop" .
Through deepening reforms, we must let the vitality of all elements of labor, knowledge, technology, management, and capital burst out, and let all the sources of social wealth flow fully.
At the same time, in order to deal with the relationship between vitality and order, social development needs to be full of vitality, but this vitality must be orderly activities.
A pool of stagnant water is not enough, nor is a turbulent undercurrent.
We need to strengthen self-confidence in the road, theory, and system, and have a rock-solid spirit and belief, as well as a strong material force to support this spirit and belief.
This depends on continuous reform and innovation, so that socialism with Chinese characteristics is more efficient than the capitalist system in liberating and developing social productive forces, liberating and enhancing social vitality, and promoting all-round development of people, and can better stimulate the enthusiasm and initiative of all the people. It can better provide favorable conditions for social development and win comparative advantages in competition, fully embodying the superiority of the socialist system with Chinese characteristics.
Third, focus on the reform of the economic system and give play to the leading role of the reform of the economic system.
The Plenary Session decided to use the "six close focus" to describe the roadmap for comprehensively deepening the reform, highlighting the focus on economic system reform and giving full play to the leading role of economic system reform.
Our country is still in and will remain in the primary stage of socialism for a long time, the basic national conditions have not changed, and the main social contradiction between the people's growing material and cultural needs and backward social production has not changed. my country is the largest developing country in the world. The status has not changed.
This determines that economic construction is still the central work of the whole party.
At present, many institutional and institutional obstacles restricting scientific development are concentrated in the economic field. The task of economic structural reform is far from being completed, and the potential of economic structural reform has not been fully released.
Adhering to the unswerving focus on economic construction, we must adhere to the unswerving focus on economic system reform.
Upper decision decided by the economic background.
