In particular, with the continuous improvement of my country's economic and social development level and people's living standards, the people's awareness of fairness, democracy, and rights has been continuously enhanced, and their reflection on social injustice has become more and more intense.
The central government has comprehensively reviewed and scientifically analyzed the current situation and situation of my country's economic and social development, and believes that if this problem is not solved quickly, it will not only affect the people's confidence in reform and opening up, but also affect social harmony and stability.
The Eighteenth National Congress of the Communist Party of China clearly stated that fairness and justice are the inherent requirements of socialism with Chinese characteristics; on the basis of the common struggle of all the people and economic and social development, we should step up the construction of a system that plays a major role in ensuring social fairness and justice, and gradually establish rights-based systems. A social equity security system with fairness, fairness of opportunity, and fairness of rules as the main content, strive to create a fair social environment, and ensure the people's equal participation and equal development rights.
The decision of the plenary meeting emphasized that comprehensively deepening reforms must take promoting social fairness and justice and improving people's well-being as the starting point and goal.
This is an inevitable requirement for upholding our party's fundamental purpose of serving the people wholeheartedly.
To comprehensively deepen reforms, we must focus on creating a fairer and just social environment, constantly overcome all kinds of phenomena that violate fairness and justice, and make more and fairer outcomes of reform and development benefit all people.
If it fails to bring tangible benefits to the common people, if it fails to create a more equitable social environment, or even leads to more injustice, the reform will be meaningless and unsustainable.
The realization of social fairness and justice is determined by many factors, the most important being the level of economic and social development.
At different levels of development and in different historical periods, people with different ideologies and strata have different understandings and demands for social fairness and justice.
When we talk about promoting social fairness and justice, we must proceed from the fundamental interests of the broadest masses of the people, look at and deal with this issue from the perspective of the level of social development, the overall situation of society, and the perspective of all the people.
Many of the phenomena that violate fairness and justice in my country at this stage are problems in development, which can be solved through continuous development, institutional arrangements, legal norms, and policy support.
We must firmly grasp the center of economic construction, promote sustainable and healthy economic development, further expand the "cake", and lay a more solid material foundation for ensuring social fairness and justice.
In this way, it does not mean that we should wait for economic development to solve the problem of social fairness and justice.
There are problems in a period of time, a society with a high level of development has problems with a high level of development, and a society with a low level of development has problems with a low level of development.
The "cake" keeps getting bigger, and at the same time, the "cake" needs to be divided.
Our society has always had the concept of "do not suffer from widowhood but suffer from inequity".
We must do our best to promote social fairness and justice on the basis of continuous development, do our best and do what we can, and strive to enable all people to have education, work, medical treatment, and old age. New progress has continued to be made in raising, housing and housing.
Regardless of the level of development, the system is an important guarantee of social fairness and justice.
Through innovative institutional arrangements, we will strive to overcome the phenomenon of violation of fairness and justice caused by human factors, and ensure the people's equal participation and equal development rights.
We should use the promotion of social fairness and justice and the improvement of people's well-being as a mirror to examine our various systems, mechanisms and policies. Where there are problems that do not conform to the promotion of social fairness and justice, reforms are needed; which areas and links are outstanding, and which areas are in which areas. Links are the focus of reform.
Issues that violate fairness and justice caused by imperfect institutional arrangements must be promptly resolved, so that our institutional arrangements better reflect the principles of socialist fairness and justice, and are more conducive to the realization, maintenance, and development of the fundamental interests of the broadest masses of the people.
Sixth, relying closely on the people to promote reform.
The people are the creators of history and the source of our strength.
The most fundamental reason why reform and opening up has won the heartfelt support and active participation of the broad masses of the people is that we have deeply rooted the cause of reform and opening up among the people from the very beginning.
The decision of the plenary session summed up the valuable experience accumulated in the reform and opening up. One of the most important ones is to emphasize the need to adhere to the people-oriented, respect the people's dominant position, give full play to the people's initiative, and rely closely on the people to promote reform.
No reform can succeed without the support and participation of the people.
No matter what difficulties and challenges we encounter, as long as there is the support and participation of the people, there will be no difficulties that cannot be overcome, and no hurdles that cannot be overcome.
We must implement the party's mass line, have a heart-to-heart relationship with the people, share weal and woe with the people, and work in unity with the people.
To advance any major reform, we must take the people's standpoint to grasp and handle major issues involving reform, and we must plan reform ideas and formulate reform measures based on the interests of the people.
Wang Fu of the Han Dynasty said: "The movement of a Dapeng is not the lightness of a feather; the speed of a Qiji is not the strength of a foot."
