Use both "invisible hand" and "visible hand"
(26 May 2014)
Making the market play a decisive role in resource allocation and better play the role of the government is both a major theoretical proposition and a major practical proposition.
Scientific understanding of this proposition and accurate grasp of its connotation are of great significance to comprehensively deepening reforms and promoting the healthy and orderly development of the socialist market economy.
On the issue of the role of the market and the role of the government, we must talk about dialectics and the two-point theory, and make good use of the "invisible hand" and "visible hand", and strive to form an organic unity, complementarity and coordination between the role of the market and the role of the government. , mutual promotion pattern, and promote the sustainable and healthy development of the economy and society.
The Third Plenary Session of the 18th Central Committee of the Communist Party of China pointed out that the reform of the economic system is the focus of comprehensively deepening the reform, and the core issue is to properly handle the relationship between the government and the market, so that the market can play a decisive role in resource allocation and the government can better play its role.
Proposing that the market should play a decisive role in the allocation of resources is a new breakthrough in our party's understanding of the laws of socialist construction with Chinese characteristics, a new achievement of the Sinicization of Marxism, and a new stage in the development of the socialist market economy. .
In order to accurately locate and grasp the decisive role of the market in resource allocation and to better play the role of the government, we must correctly understand the relationship between the role of the market and the role of the government.
The relationship between the government and the market is the core issue of my country's economic system reform.
The Third Plenary of the 18th Central Committee of the Communist Party of China revised the fundamental role of the market in the allocation of resources to a decisive role. Although there is only a difference of two characters, it is a brand-new positioning for the role of the market. "These two positions are connected and developed in succession.
Let the market play a decisive role in resource allocation and better play the role of the government, the two are organically unified, not mutually negating, and the two cannot be separated and opposed, and the decisive role of the market in resource allocation cannot be used. It is impossible to replace or even deny the role of the government by better exerting the role of the government to make the market play a decisive role in resource allocation.
Proposing to make the market play a decisive role in resource allocation is actually implementing the problem orientation.
After more than 20 years of practice, my country's socialist market economic system has continued to develop, but there are still many problems. There are still many drawbacks that restrict the vitality of market entities and hinder the market and the law of value from fully functioning.
If these problems are not solved well, it will be difficult to form a perfect socialist market economic system, and it will be difficult to change the development mode and adjust the economic structure.
We must adhere to the direction of socialist market economic reform, promote market-oriented reform in breadth and depth, reduce the direct allocation of resources by the government, reduce the direct intervention of the government in microeconomic activities, and accelerate the construction of a unified, open, competitive and orderly market system. Establish fair, open and transparent market rules, hand over economic activities that can be effectively regulated by market mechanisms to the market, and leave things that the government should not manage to the market, so that the market can fully play its role in all areas where it can play a role, and promote the realization of resource allocation. Maximize benefits and optimize efficiency, so that enterprises and individuals have more vitality and more space to develop the economy and create wealth.
Scientific macro-control and effective government governance are the inherent requirements to give full play to the advantages of the socialist market economy system.
To better play the role of the government, it is necessary to effectively transform government functions, deepen the reform of the administrative system, innovate administrative management methods, improve the macro-control system, strengthen the supervision of market activities, strengthen and optimize public services, promote social fairness and justice and social stability, and promote common prosperity. .
Governments at all levels must administer strictly in accordance with the law, and earnestly perform their duties. The things that should be managed must be managed well and in place, and the powers that should be delegated must be fully and fully in place, and resolutely overcome the dislocation, offside, and absence of government functions.
Adhering to the leadership of the party and giving full play to the party's core role of leading the overall situation and coordinating all parties is an important feature of my country's socialist market economic system.
Over the past 30 years of reform and opening up, the reason why my country's economic and social development has been able to achieve great achievements that are rarely seen in the world, and the reason why our people's living standards have been able to greatly improve, is because of our unswerving adherence to the party's leadership and giving full play to the party organizations at all levels. The role of all party members is inseparable.
In our country, the strong and strong leadership of the party is the fundamental guarantee for the government to play its role.
In the process of comprehensively deepening the reform, we must adhere to and develop our political advantages, use our political advantages to lead and advance reform, mobilize the enthusiasm of all parties, and promote the continuous improvement of the socialist market economic system and the better development of the socialist market economy.
Under the new situation, cadres at all levels, especially leading cadres, should insist on deepening learning in practice, deepening practice in learning, constantly studying new problems, summarizing new experiences, and learning to correctly use the "invisible hand" and "visible hand". ” to become an expert at navigating the relationship between the government and the market.
